# Building the Future of UMKM Websites: SEO & AI Optimization Strategy (Case Study: One Creative) 🚀

📅 **May 03, 2026**

In the process of developing the website for [**One Creative**](https://www.onecreative.id), I realized that the standards for UMKM (MSME) websites have changed drastically. If before we only focused on the website being "accessible," we must now ensure that the website is friendly to traditional search engines like Google and ready for the era of **Generative Engine Optimization (GEO)** for AI like ChatGPT and Gemini.

This article will discuss the behind-the-scenes process of how I designed the digital strategy for [**One Creative**](https://www.onecreative.id) so that it is not just a showcase, but also a smart business growth engine.

---

### 1. Evolution from SEO to GEO (Generative Engine Optimization)

Today, potential customers don't just search on Google; they ask AI. *"Where is the best place to print invitations in Bau-Bau?"* is a question often asked to ChatGPT.

To ensure [**One Creative**](https://www.onecreative.id) is recommended by AI, I implemented:
- **Structured Data (JSON-LD)**: I provide a "digital business card" that machines can read. With a complete schema, AI can technically validate that [**One Creative**](https://www.onecreative.id) is a credible, real business entity.
- **Contextual FAQ Features**: AI looks for direct answers. By creating an FAQ section that answers specific customer needs, we provide high-quality "bait" for AI to pull that information as a source for answers.

### 2. A "Clean" Technical Foundation with Astro Framework

Speed is a signal of trust, for both humans and machines. I chose to use the [**Astro Framework**](https://astro.build) for [**One Creative**](https://www.onecreative.id) because of its performance-focused approach.

- **Static Site Generation (SSG)**: Content is delivered in pure HTML form. AI robots and Google crawlers don't have to struggle with heavy scripts, making indexing much faster and more accurate.
- **Maximum Performance Scores**: A lightweight website means a better user experience, especially for customers accessing via mobile networks in regional areas.

### 3. Building Authority (E-E-A-T)

Google and AI now evaluate *Experience, Expertise, Authoritativeness,* and *Trustworthiness*. At [**One Creative**](https://www.onecreative.id), I ensure these elements are present both visually and technically:
- **Social Proof (Testimonials)**: Customer reviews are processed to provide positive signals to AI algorithms about service satisfaction levels.
- **Data Consistency (NAP)**: Ensuring Name, Address, and Phone number are consistent across all digital platforms to build a strong "knowledge graph."

### 4. Conversion Bridge: WhatsApp

In the Indonesian UMKM market, a website is a **trust showcase**, while WhatsApp is the **cashier**. The strategy I implemented at [**One Creative**](https://www.onecreative.id) is to facilitate the transition from information-seeking visitors to transaction-ready customers through intuitive WhatsApp button integration.

---

### Conclusion: A Website is a Long-Term Investment

Building a website is not just about aesthetics; it's about building an adaptive digital foundation. With the right technology and structured content strategy, UMKMs like [**One Creative**](https://www.onecreative.id) are ready to compete in the age of artificial intelligence.

If you want to learn more about this strategy, I have compiled a complete guide here: [UMKM Strategy Guide: SEO & AI](https://www.onecreative.id/blog/strategi-seo-ai).

